preflight.check:
Run the following in a fresh PowerShell window:
  $missing = @()
  if (-not $env:VIKUNJA_URL)  { $missing += 'VIKUNJA_URL'  }
  if (-not $env:VIKUNJA_USER) { $missing += 'VIKUNJA_USER' }
  if (-not $env:VIKUNJA_PASS) { $missing += 'VIKUNJA_PASS' }
  if ($missing.Count -gt 0) { Write-Host "MISSING: $($missing -join ', ')" } else { Write-Host "ALL SET" }

If ANY var is missing: HARD STOP. Report to Guide.
All three must be non-null/non-empty before any script edit.

edit.instruction:
UPDATE header comment (lines 8-10): OLD: "# Auth: reads Vikunja credentials from .mcp.json at the repo root # (same pattern as la_merge_approve.ps1). .mcp.json is gitignored and # ACL-locked to the user account that owns the credentials." NEW: "# Auth: reads Vikunja credentials directly from VIKUNJA_URL / # VIKUNJA_USER / VIKUNJA_PASS User-scope env vars (Ticket II)."
REMOVE the $McpConfigPath derivation line (line ~26): $McpConfigPath = Join-Path $RepoRoot '.mcp.json' (Keep the preceding Stage 2.5 g5-9 comment block if it provides useful context, but if it only explains the .mcp.json derivation, remove it too.)
REPLACE the Step 1 Vikunja auth block (lines ~34-52, the Test-Path + ConvertFrom-Json block): OLD pattern: # Step 1: Vikunja auth (via .mcp.json) # ------------------------------------------------------------------- if (-not (Test-Path $McpConfigPath)) { Write-Log "ABORT: .mcp.json not found at $McpConfigPath" exit 0 } try { $mcp = Get-Content $McpConfigPath -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json $vikUrl = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_URL $vikUser = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_USER $vikPass = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_PASS if (-not $vikUrl -or -not $vikUser -or -not $vikPass) { Write-Log "ABORT: .mcp.json missing VIKUNJA_URL / VIKUNJA_USER / VIKUNJA_PASS" exit 0 } } catch { Write-Log "ABORT: failed to parse .mcp.json: $_" exit 0 }
NEW (replace with): # Step 1: Vikunja auth (direct env-var — Ticket II) # ------------------------------------------------------------------- $vikUrl = $env:VIKUNJA_URL $vikUser = $env:VIKUNJA_USER $vikPass = $env:VIKUNJA_PASS if (-not $vikUrl -or -not $vikUser -or -not $vikPass) { Write-Log "ABORT: VIKUNJA_URL / VIKUNJA_USER / VIKUNJA_PASS env vars not set" exit 0 }
NOTE: Keep $RepoRoot param in the param block unchanged (may be passed by Task Scheduler callers; removing it from the signature could break registered tasks). It simply becomes unused in this script after removing $McpConfigPath.

REPLACE the credential block (lines ~38-56, the .mcp.json read):
  OLD pattern (comment + Test-Path + ConvertFrom-Json block):
    # Vikunja credentials live in the same .mcp.json the wake_launcher reads.
    $mcpConfigPath = Join-Path $RepoRoot '.mcp.json'
    if (-not (Test-Path $mcpConfigPath)) {
        Write-Output "ESCALATION-WATCHDOG: .mcp.json absent at $mcpConfigPath; exit silently."
        exit 0
    }
    try {
        $mcp = Get-Content $mcpConfigPath -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
        $vikUrl  = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_URL
        $vikUser = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_USER
        $vikPass = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_PASS
        if (-not $vikUrl -or -not $vikUser -or -not $vikPass) {
            Write-Output "ESCALATION-WATCHDOG: .mcp.json missing Vikunja credentials; exit silently."
            exit 0
        }
    } catch {
        Write-Output "ESCALATION-WATCHDOG: failed to parse .mcp.json: $_"
        exit 0
    }

  NEW:
    # Vikunja credentials from env vars (Ticket II).
    $vikUrl  = $env:VIKUNJA_URL
    $vikUser = $env:VIKUNJA_USER
    $vikPass = $env:VIKUNJA_PASS
    if (-not $vikUrl -or -not $vikUser -or -not $vikPass) {
        Write-Output "ESCALATION-WATCHDOG: VIKUNJA_URL / VIKUNJA_USER / VIKUNJA_PASS env vars not set; exit silently."
        exit 0
    }

NOTE: line ~106 uses $vikUser: "$laUsername = $vikUser  # current MCP user IS the LA's user"
This is PRESERVED — $vikUser is still set by the new block.

REPLACE the 4-line credential block at lines ~210-213: OLD: $mcp = Get-Content (Join-Path $RepoRoot '.mcp.json') -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json $vikUrl = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_URL $vikUser = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_USER $vikPass = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_PASS
NEW: $vikUrl = $env:VIKUNJA_URL $vikUser = $env:VIKUNJA_USER $vikPass = $env:VIKUNJA_PASS if (-not $vikUrl -or -not $vikUser -or -not $vikPass) { throw 'VIKUNJA_URL / VIKUNJA_USER / VIKUNJA_PASS env vars not set' }
NOTE: This is a test script (not a scheduled task), so throw on missing env vars is appropriate — a failed test should be noisy, not silently exit.

Target: Test-WorkAvailable function (line ~290).

STEP A — Remove $McpConfigPath parameter from function signature (line ~295):
  OLD: [string]$McpConfigPath = 'C:\Users\mrbla\BlarAI\.mcp.json'
  NEW: (remove this line entirely)

  VERIFY FIRST: search wake_launcher.ps1 for all call sites of Test-WorkAvailable.
  The only call site is at line ~853:
    if (-not (Test-WorkAvailable -Role $Role -RepoRoot $RepoRoot)) {
  This call does NOT pass -McpConfigPath → safe to remove the parameter.
  If any OTHER call site passes -McpConfigPath, HARD STOP and report to Guide.

STEP B — Replace Step 2 credential block (lines ~374-400):
  OLD pattern (inside Test-WorkAvailable, Step 2):
    # Step 2: Vikunja label probe.
    if (-not (Test-Path $McpConfigPath)) {
        Write-Log "WORK-GATE: .mcp.json absent at $McpConfigPath; fail-open (run Claude)."
        return $true
    }
    try {
        $mcp = Get-Content $McpConfigPath -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
        $vikUrl  = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_URL
        $vikUser = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_USER
        $vikPass = $mcp.mcpServers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_PASS
        if (-not $vikUrl -or -not $vikUser -or -not $vikPass) {
            Write-Log "WORK-GATE: .mcp.json missing Vikunja credentials; fail-open (run Claude)."
            return $true
        }
    } catch {
        Write-Log "WORK-GATE: failed to parse .mcp.json; fail-open. $_"
        return $true
    }
    try {
        $loginBody = @{ username = $vikUser; password = $vikPass } | ConvertTo-Json
        $loginResp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "$vikUrl/api/v1/login" -Method Post -Body $loginBody -ContentType 'application/json' -TimeoutSec 10
        $token = $loginResp.token
        $authHeaders = @{ 'Authorization' = "Bearer $token" }
    } catch {
        Write-Log "WORK-GATE: Vikunja login failed; fail-open. $_"
        return $true
    }

  NEW (replace entire block above):
    # Step 2: Vikunja label probe.
    $vikUrl  = $env:VIKUNJA_URL
    $vikUser = $env:VIKUNJA_USER
    $vikPass = $env:VIKUNJA_PASS
    if (-not $vikUrl -or -not $vikUser -or -not $vikPass) {
        Write-Log "WORK-GATE: VIKUNJA_URL / VIKUNJA_USER / VIKUNJA_PASS env vars not set; fail-open (run Claude)."
        return $true
    }
    try {
        $loginBody = @{ username = $vikUser; password = $vikPass } | ConvertTo-Json
        $loginResp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "$vikUrl/api/v1/login" -Method Post -Body $loginBody -ContentType 'application/json' -TimeoutSec 10
        $token = $loginResp.token
        $authHeaders = @{ 'Authorization' = "Bearer $token" }
    } catch {
        Write-Log "WORK-GATE: Vikunja login failed; fail-open. $_"
        return $true
    }

  IMPORTANT: Maintain fail-open semantics (return $true) for wake_launcher.
  If env vars missing → fail-open. If login fails → fail-open.
  Rationale: work-gate auth failure should fire Claude (miss some work) rather than
  silently block all work. This matches the pre-refactor .mcp.json-absent behaviour.
